    • Method Detail

      • getVirtualProcessingUnits

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<SchedulableResource> getVirtualProcessingUnits()
        Returns the value of the 'Virtual Processing Units' reference list. The list contents are of type SchedulableResource. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Dependent Scheduler'.

        If the meaning of the 'Virtual Processing Units' reference list isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

        Returns:
        the value of the 'Virtual Processing Units' reference list.
        See Also:
        GRMPackage.getSecondaryScheduler_VirtualProcessingUnits(), SchedulableResource.getDependentScheduler()
